spans.text: celestial TRUTH appear : Serene her Brow
bad the Fabric rise , And spread the azure Mantle of the Skies
near — But why thus walk we , mindless of our Ease , Exposed beneath the Sun's meridian Blaze
murmuring by , And tuneful Birds their sylvan Notes apply
waving Shades beneath the Poplar Bough
So cool the Stream , the flowery Banks so sweet , DIANA's Self
what she said , approached the Brook
Her own infernal Robe far left
gains Admittance to the Rich and Great
spoke and looked with such a graceful Air , Mistaken FAME pronounced her Wise and Fair
all his lewd Attempts with Love
a Share , While FALSHOOD's Self admired her Influence there
a Habit , so unlike the lost
lonely Fields and Cells , Where Silence reigns , and Contemplation dwells
